  15:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c **** /*
  16:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****   Parse LoadedImage options area, called only in case the regular
  17:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****   shell protos are not available.
  18:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c **** 
  19:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****   Format of LoadedImage->LoadOptions appears to be a
  20:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****   single-space-separated list of args (looks like the shell already
  21:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****   pre-parses the input, it apparently folds several consecutive spaces
  22:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****   into one):
  23:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****     argv[0] space argv[1] (etc.) argv[N] space \0 cwd \0 other data
  24:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****   For safety, we support the trailing \0 without a space before, as
  25:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c ****   well as several consecutive spaces (-> several args).
  26:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/cmdline.c **** */
